$ Python standard library: tkinter
@ tkinter

`tkinter` allows to use the → development/languages/TCL[Tcl]/Tk GUI toolkit from → development/languages/Python.

{ Installing tkinter

  Because `tkinter` relies on the Tcl/Tk toolkit, `tkinter` might not be installed togeter with a default Python installation, even though `tkinter` belongs to
  → development/languages/Python/standard-library[Python's standard library].

  → https://stackoverflow.com/a/25905642/180275[This Stackoverflow answer] and its comments suggest to install `tkinter` like so:
  table { ll
     Apt based distros (Ubuntu, Debian) ☰ `sudo apt-get install python3-tk`
     Fedora ☰ `sudo dnf install python3-tkinter`
     macOS ☰ `brew install python-tk`
  table }

}
{ Checking if tkinter is properly installed

code {
$ python → development/languages/Python/import-system/minus-m[-m] tkinter
code }

}

sa:
  → development/languages/Python/libraries/wxPython[`wxPython`]
